article.description: Tucker Haymond scored 13 points and Western Michigan topped Liberty 68-58 in the Challenge in Music City tournament on Friday.
article.headline: Western Michigan handles Liberty 68-58
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Tucker Haymond scored 13 points and Western Michigan topped Liberty 68-58 in the Challenge in Music City tournament on Friday. Anthony Avery Jr. had 14 points with six rebounds for the Broncos (3-3) and Kellen McCormick added 12 points and six boards. Ryan Kemrite led Liberty (3-3) with 15 points -- including four 3-pointers. Ezra Talbert and Caleb Homesley scored 11 points apiece while Lovell Cabbil added 10 points. Western Michigan outrebounded the Flames 34-19. Liberty led early, thanks to three straight 3-pointers by Homesley, but a 13-3 run by the Broncos led to a 33-25 lead at the break. Kemrite's 3-pointer with 7:16 left made it a two-point game, but Western Michigan responded with an 11-3 run -- including a 3-pointer by Jared Klein and a 3-point play by Haymond on a jump shot -- to put the game away.
